<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>LiveTemplate — Upload Modes</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="{{lvtClientStyleURL}}" />
  <style>
    body { font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; max-width: 760px; margin: 2rem auto; padding: 0 1rem; }
    .mode { border: 1px solid #ddd; border-radius: 8px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem; margin: 1rem 0; }
    .mode h2 { margin: 0 0 .25rem; font-size: 1.05rem; }
    .mode p { margin: .25rem 0 .75rem; color: #555; font-size: .9rem; }
    .result { font-family: ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: .8rem; color: #0a7; word-break: break-all; }
    img[data-lvt-upload-preview] { max-width: 160px; max-height: 160px; display: block; margin-top: .5rem; }
    .thumb { max-width: 160px; max-height: 160px; display: block; margin-top: .5rem; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Upload modes</h1>
  <p>Four upload destinations, one <code>lvt-upload</code> attribute. The mode is chosen entirely by server config.</p>

  <div class="mode">
    <h2>Direct</h2>
    <p>Browser uploads straight to storage via a presigned URL — bytes never touch the server.</p>
    <input type="file" lvt-upload="direct" accept="image/*" />
    {{if .DirectRef}}<div class="result" id="direct-result">stored: {{.DirectRef}}</div>
    <img class="thumb" src="{{.DirectRef}}" alt="direct upload" />{{end}}
  </div>

  <div class="mode">
    <h2>Proxied</h2>
    <p>Bytes stream through the server to storage with zero local-disk staging. The
       record id below rides along in the same multipart POST, ahead of the file
       part, so <code>OnUpload</code> reads it mid-stream and routes the bytes per record.</p>
    <form>
      <label>Record id <input type="text" name="record_id" id="proxied-record-id" placeholder="e.g. invoice-7" /></label>
      <input type="file" lvt-upload="proxied" accept="image/*" />
    </form>
    {{if .ProxiedRef}}<div class="result" id="proxied-result">stored: {{.ProxiedRef}}</div>
    <img class="thumb" src="{{.ProxiedRef}}" alt="proxied upload" />{{end}}
  </div>

  <div class="mode">
    <h2>Volume</h2>
    <p>Bytes are staged to a retained directory on the server (the app owns the path).</p>
    <input type="file" lvt-upload="volume" accept="image/*" />
    {{if .VolumePath}}<div class="result" id="volume-result">saved: {{.VolumePath}}</div>{{end}}
  </div>

  <div class="mode">
    <h2>Preview</h2>
    <p>The file stays on the device; only metadata reaches the server. The preview below is local.</p>
    <input type="file" lvt-upload="preview" accept="image/*" />
    {{.lvt.UploadPreview "preview"}}
  </div>

  <script src="{{lvtClientScriptURL}}"></script>
</body>
</html>
